definitions.definition: The achievement of one's aim or goal .
examples: His third attempt to pass the entrance exam was a success .
Don't let success go to your head.

definitions.definition: One who, or that which, achieves assumed goals.
examples: The new range of toys has been a resounding success .

definitions.definition: The fact of getting or achieving wealth , respect , or fame .
examples: She is country music's most recent success .

definitions.definition: Something which happens as a consequence ; the outcome or result .

main_definition: The achievement of one's aim or goal . [from 16th c.]
secondary_definitions: One who, or that which, achieves assumed goals.
The fact of getting or achieving wealth , respect , or fame .
( obsolete ) Something which happens as a consequence ; the outcome or result . [16th–18th c.]
